+3s say speaker="Lloyd McKenzie" text="Any other business before we close?"
+3s say speaker="David Hay" text="Quick plug — I've updated the Hay on FHIR blog with a post about the R6 normative timeline. If people could share it, that would help raise awareness about the November content freeze."
+2s say speaker="Grahame Grieve" text="Is it 'Hay on FHIR' or 'FHIR and Hay'? I can never remember."
+2s say speaker="David Hay" text="It's Hay on FHIR, Grahame. It's been Hay on FHIR for ten years. You were at the naming meeting."
+2s say speaker="Grahame Grieve" text="I've been to a lot of naming meetings. Most of the names were better than 'Hay on FHIR.'"
+2s say speaker="David Hay" text="Says the man who named the spec after a misspelling."
+2s say speaker="Eric Haas" text="FHIR — Fast Healthcare Interoperability Resources. Or as I like to call it, Finally Healthcare Interoperability... Remains. Elusive."
+2s say speaker="Lloyd McKenzie" text="And on that deeply encouraging note — meeting adjourned. See everyone next Monday."

+2s chat id=chat-14 from="Simone Heckmann" to="Everyone" text="Frohe FHIRtage to those of us already thinking about the holidays."
